March 1, 1965. No. 18,

Original.

Illinois v. Missouri. William G. Clark, Attorney General of Illinois, Richard A. Michael, Assistant Attorney General, and Terence F. MacCarthy, Special Assistant Attorney General, for plaintiff! Norman H. Anderson, Attorney General of Missouri, and J. Gordon Siddens and Howard L. McFadden, Assistant Attorneys General, for defendant.

State of Illinois directed to file reply to response within 30 days.

[For earlier order herein, see 379 U. S. 952.]
